                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2540/8.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Fox</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 18, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Fox informs Mr. Root, referring to previous correspondence<note n="a"
                        xml:id="d284fna">Not printed.</note> eight, twelve, and also fifteen, that
                    the railway crisis is reached, and that revolution is imminent owing to the
                    railway problem. He also states that the American investments are reported as
                    being in danger, the people insisting on confiscation. He further states that
                    the railway company urges arbitration of her contract. He asks for
                    instructions.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
